You cannot infer a precise production speedup from a 4x microbenchmark alone. Use Amdahl’s law:

full-path speedup = 1 / ((1 - p) + p / 4)

where p is the fraction of end-to-end production request time originally spent in that loop.

Examples: p = 0.25 -> 1.33x, p = 0.50 -> 1.60x, p = 0.80 -> 2.50x. The upper bound is 4x, and only if that loop was effectively 100% of request time.

So the precise expected production speedup is not a single number from the microbenchmark; it is whatever that formula gives after you measure p with production profiling.You cannot infer a precise production speedup from a 4x microbenchmark alone. Use Amdahl’s law:

